The paper focuses on developing a reinforcement learning protocol for a multiagent coordination task, which falls under the category of multiagent systems (cs.MA). The use of Q-learning and the analysis of the dynamics and communication protocols also suggest a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of a game theory framework, specifically the iterated prisoner's dilemma, suggests a potential fit for the game theory sub-category (cs.GT). Finally, the focus on understanding the behavior and interactions of multiple agents suggests a potential fit for the systems and control sub-category (cs.SY).
